President Biden invited leading business people to the Oval Office to discuss the state of the economy, the recovery package, infrastructure, and the minimum wage. He acknowledged that many Americans are struggling, with unemployment, housing insecurity, lack of healthcare, and children not in school. President Biden expressed his desire to work with Republicans and Democrats to address these issues and emphasized the need to control the coronavirus while also focusing on economic growth. He stated that his priority is to keep people safe and address the urgent needs of the American people. When asked about the impeachment trial of former President Trump, President Biden stated that he will not be watching the trial as he has a job to do. He also briefly commented on the Democrats' proposal regarding a $75,000 cap but did not provide further details.